<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-06-03T04:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-06-03T04:00:00-05:00" n="203" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d203">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60D/232: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Finland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">McClintock</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Helsinki</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-06-03T11:00:00+02:00">June
                                        3, 1943—11 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 1:39 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>784. The Swiss Minister last night told me he and his wife had
                                lunched alone with President and Mrs. Ryti on June 1. Mr. Egger said
                                he had asked the President about relations with the United States.
                                Ryti replied that Finland could do nothing; that its fate rested
                                with the decision of the great powers. As for the United States it
                                might, <pb facs="0292" n="280" xml:id="pg_280"/> if it wanted to
                                please the Russians, acquiesce in the USSR doing what it wished with
                                Finland. The President concluded by saying “The Americans have
                                offered us only words. The Germans have given us bread”. In this
                                brief description you have a precisely accurate picture of the frame
                                of mind which now dominates the makers of policy in this
                                country.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">McClintock</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>